Would you like me to compare this with the Northern CA options or discuss the specific benefits in more detail?`;
  }

  // Check for specific Vision questions
  if (lowerMessage.includes('vision benefits') || lowerMessage.includes('eye care') || lowerMessage.includes('vision coverage') || lowerMessage.includes('vision plan')) {
    return `Excellent question about vision coverage! I can see you have the AmeriVet Partners Management vision plan. Here's the complete analysis:

**👁️ Vision Benefits Analysis (AmeriVet Partners Management):**

**Plan Overview:**
• **Provider**: AmeriVet Partners Management
• **Coverage Type**: Vision insurance
• **Network**: VSP or similar vision network
• **Coverage Period**: 2024-2025

**Coverage Details:**
• **Annual Eye Exams** - Usually 100% covered
• **Frames Allowance** - Typically $150-$200 every 2 years
• **Lens Coverage** - Basic lenses often 100% covered
• **Contact Lenses** - Usually covered with allowance
• **LASIK Discounts** - Often 15-20% off procedures

**Typical Vision Plan Features:**
• **Network Providers** - VSP or similar network
• **Out-of-Network** - Usually 80% coverage up to allowance
• **Progressive Lenses** - Often covered with upgrade fees
• **Tinted Lenses** - Usually covered for medical necessity
• **Contact Lens Fitting** - Often covered annually

**Cost Considerations:**
• **Annual Maximum** - Usually $200-$300 per person
• **Co-pays** - $10-$25 for exams
• **Upgrades** - Pay difference for premium frames/lenses
• **Frequency** - New glasses every 1-2 years

**Smart Vision Strategy:**
• Use annual benefits before they expire
• Consider HSA funds for upgrades
• Keep receipts for tax purposes
• Check network providers for best coverage

**Coverage Highlights:**
• **Preventive Care** - Annual eye exams
• **Corrective Lenses** - Glasses and contacts
• **Surgical Procedures** - LASIK discounts
