  // Check for specific HSA questions
  if (lowerMessage.includes('hsa contribution') || lowerMessage.includes('hsa limits') || lowerMessage.includes('hsa investment') || lowerMessage.includes('hsa rules')) {
    return `Excellent question about HSA rules and contributions! Let me explain everything you need to know:

**💰 HSA Complete Guide:**

**📊 HSA Contribution Limits (2024):**
• **Individual**: $4,300 maximum
• **Family**: $8,550 maximum
• **Catch-up (55+)**: Additional $1,000
• **Employer Contributions**: May contribute on your behalf

**💡 HSA Contribution Strategies:**
• **Maximize Contributions**: Contribute up to the limit
• **Employer Match**: Take advantage of employer contributions
• **Catch-up Contributions**: Additional $1,000 if 55+
• **Timing**: Contribute early in the year for maximum growth

**🏦 HSA Investment Options:**
• **Cash Account**: FDIC insured, no risk
• **Investment Options**: Mutual funds, ETFs
• **Growth Potential**: Long-term wealth building
• **Retirement Planning**: HSA becomes like 401k at 65

**📋 HSA Qualified Expenses:**
• **Medical Expenses**: Doctor visits, prescriptions
• **Dental Expenses**: Cleanings, fillings, orthodontics
• **Vision Expenses**: Eye exams, glasses, contacts
• **Mental Health**: Therapy, counseling
• **Alternative Medicine**: Acupuncture, chiropractic

**🎯 HSA Tax Advantages:**
• **Pre-Tax Contributions**: Reduce taxable income
• **Tax-Free Growth**: Interest and investments grow tax-free
• **Tax-Free Withdrawals**: For qualified medical expenses
• **Triple Tax Advantage**: Only HSA offers this benefit

**💼 HSA Rules & Regulations:**
• **HDHP Requirement**: Must have high-deductible health plan
• **No Other Coverage**: Can't have other health coverage
• **Rollover**: Funds roll over year to year
• **Portable**: Take HSA with you if you change jobs

**🔍 HSA vs FSA vs HRA:**
• **HSA**: Triple tax advantage, rollover, portable
• **FSA**: Use it or lose it, employer-owned
• **HRA**: Employer-owned, not portable

**📈 HSA Investment Strategy:**
• **Start with Cash**: Build emergency fund first
• **Diversify**: Mix of stocks, bonds, cash
• **Long-term Focus**: HSA is for retirement planning
• **Rebalance**: Adjust allocation over time

**💡 HSA Tips:**
• **Keep Receipts**: Document all qualified expenses
• **Don't Withdraw**: Let funds grow for retirement
• **Use for Retirement**: HSA becomes like 401k at 65
• **Plan Ahead**: Consider future medical expenses

Would you like me to explain HSA investment strategies or discuss how to maximize your HSA contributions?`;
