What specific aspect would you like to know more about?`;
  }

  if (lowerMessage.includes('fsa') || lowerMessage.includes('flexible spending')) {
    return `FSAs are fantastic for healthcare savings! Let me explain how they work:

**Flexible Spending Account (FSA):**
• Pre-tax contributions (saves you money on taxes!)
• Use it or lose it (spend by March 15th of next year)
• 2024 limit: $3,200 per year
• Covers medical expenses, prescriptions, dental, vision

**Key differences from HSA:**
• FSA: Use it or lose it, no investment options
• HSA: Keep forever, can invest, triple tax advantage
• You can't have both FSA and HSA (unless limited FSA)

**Smart FSA strategy:**
• Estimate your annual medical expenses
• Contribute slightly less to avoid forfeiture
• Use for predictable expenses (prescriptions, contacts, etc.)

Would you like help calculating your optimal FSA contribution?`;
